1 Section 1. Section 49-1474.01, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska,
2 is amended to read:
3 49-1474.01 (1) The person, except an individual or individuals
4 acting independently utilizing their own personal resources, who pays for
5 the production, distribution, or posting of a billboard, placard, poster,
6 pamphlet, or other printed matter relating to a candidate or ballot
7 question shall cause a disclaimer containing the name and street address
8 or post office box number of the person to appear on such matter. The
9 person who pays for a radio or television advertisement relating to a
10 candidate or ballot question shall cause a disclaimer containing the name
11 of such person to be included in the advertisement, and the radio or
12 television station shall, for a period of at least six months, keep the
13 street address or post office box number of such person on file and
14 divulge it to any person upon request.
15 (2) The size and placement of the disclaimer shall be determined by
16 rules and regulations adopted and promulgated by the commission. The
17 rules and regulations shall exempt from the disclaimer required by this
18 section windshield stickers, yard signs, bumper stickers, campaign
19 buttons, and balloons and may also exempt other items relating to a
20 candidate or committee which are printed or reproduced at the request of
21 such candidate or committee.
22 (3) Any person who knowingly violates the provisions of this section
23 shall be guilty of a Class IV misdemeanor.
24 Sec. 2. Original section 49-1474.01, Reissue Revised Statutes of
25 Nebraska, is repealed.
